DOCUMENT(7)        A/UX Workstation Local Commands         DOCUMENT(7)

NAME
     DOCUMENT - manual for the local command set on this A/UX 3.1.1
     workstation (QEMU q800 guest "auxvm" and the SE/30 "jobs")

DESCRIPTION
     This machine carries a modern terminal stack and a set of local
     tools layered over stock A/UX 3.1.1: ncurses 5.7, rxvt 2.6.4, an
     X11R6 client library build, and the utilities below.  Everything
     here is mirrored, with sources and build notes, in the se30
     repository on the controlling Mac (~/se30).

     System layout:
       /usr/local/gcc-2.7.2.3        gcc 2.7.2.3 (drive via
                                     -B/usr/local/gcc-2.7.2.3/)
       /usr/local/ncurses-5.7        ncurses, terminfo db (2650 entries)
       /usr/local/xcb/xc             X11R6 source tree (headers)
       /usr/local/r6lib              X11R6 import libs incl. the split
                                     libX11{a,b,c}_s.a archives
       /shlib                        runtime shared libraries
       /usr/local/src/dialc          dialc sources
       /usr/local/src/rxvt           rxvt 2.6.4 sources
       /usr/lib/X11/fonts/profont    ProFont SNF + BDF sources

ENVIRONMENT
     TERMINFO=/usr/local/ncurses-5.7/share/terminfo must be exported
     for every curses program (set in /.bashrc).  The X font path
     gains /usr/lib/X11/fonts/profont in /.x11start.

COMMANDS
   auxtop
     Themed ncurses process monitor (htop-style) reading the kernel
     via /dev/kmem through the top 3.5 machine module.  Live CPU,
     memory, and swap meters; process table sorted by size.
     Keys: q quit, space refresh, i toggle idle processes.
     Theme: /.auxtoprc (title/text/accent/bar/header/status = ANSI
     color names); defaults to the C89 SUMMER synthwave palette.
     auxtop-x launches it in a themed rxvt (fvwm menu entry).

   dialc
     Terminal client for the Dialtone AOL 3.x revival network
     (production dialtone.live:5190).  P3 wire protocol, FDO codec,
     chat, instant messages, news reader, multi-window ncurses UI.
       dialc [-v] [-p] [user] [pass] [host] [port]
     Without credentials an AOL-style sign-on form appears.  -p plain
     line mode (pipes/tests), -v adds P3 wire tracing (implies -p).
     Commands: /chat /im <name> <text> /news <1-5> /w <n> /leave /quit
     Keys: esc-<n> jump to window n, esc-0 main menu, ctrl-n/ctrl-p
     cycle, arrows scroll or select, pgup/pgdn page, ctrl-l repaint.
     dialc-x launches it in a themed rxvt ("dialtone" on the fvwm
     menu).  Canonical source: github.com/iconidentify/dialc; A/UX
     build recipe in ~/se30/dialc/README.md on the Mac.

   rxvt
     rxvt 2.6.4, ported to A/UX against the R6 client libraries.
     VT102 + 8-color ANSI terminal; sets TERM=rxvt (entry present in
     the local terminfo db).  Installed setuid root for pty access.
     Replaces the 1994 R6 xterm, whose clear/scroll/addressing escape
     handling corrupts ncurses output.  Resources under Rxvt* in
     /.Xdefaults (synthwave palette, visualBell - see CAVEATS).
     Port notes and build recipe: ~/se30/rxvt/README.md on the Mac.

   auxfont theme
     One-shot desktop font switcher.  Themes: profont (terminals
     profont15, chrome profont12), profont-big (profont17),
     profont-small (profont12), fixed (7x13 / lucidatypewriter).
     Rewrites Rxvt*/XTerm* font resources in /.Xdefaults, Font and
     WindowFont plus every -fn flag in /.fvwmrc, the auxtop-x and
     dialc-x launchers, and the gtk font in /.gtkrc; then runs
     xrdb -merge and sync(1).  Restart fvwm and open new terminals
     to see the change.  ProFont is served as SNF (the XmacII server
     is R4-era; compile new fonts with /usr/bin/X11/bdftosnf, then
     mkfontdir and xset fp rehash).

   auxagent / auxadmin
     Remote-exec and file-transfer agent (AAP over HTTP/1.0) on port
     8377, boot-persistent via /etc/inittab.  Driven from the Mac
     with auxctl: ping, exec, get, put, admin.  auxadmin manages
     workstation settings (autologin, session type).  One request per
     connection; transfers carry CRC-32.  See ~/se30/auxagent.

   auxfetch, auxsaver, bgroot
     Desktop furniture: neofetch-style system summary; the bouncing
     DVD-logo screensaver; root-window background setter (XPM) used
     by the fvwm Appearance menu.

X SESSION
     fvwm 1.24r is the session anchor (config /.fvwmrc).  The Main
     menu (mouse 1 on root, or F1) carries Terminal, dialtone,
     auxtop, SimCity, Quake, and the Appearance submenus.  All
     terminal entries launch rxvt with the synthwave theme.  Restart
     fvwm from the logout popup to pick up config changes.

CAVEATS
     o  Crashes can revert unsynced filesystem writes.  Run sync(1)
        after editing anything you care about.
     o  A running binary cannot be overwritten or unlinked ("text
        file busy"); mv it aside, then cp the replacement.
     o  The audible bell can crash the emulator (QEMU -audio none vs
        the q800 sound chip).  Keep visualBell true in /.Xdefaults
        and leave xset b off in /.x11start.
     o  The tty driver post-processes output (ONLCR, TAB3): curses
        programs must disable OPOST or cursor motion scrambles.
        dialc does this itself; see ~/se30/dialc/aux_termfix.c.
     o  The stock R6 xterm misimplements clears, scroll regions, and
        relative cursor addressing.  Use rxvt for curses programs;
        under xterm, dialc and auxtop defeat the broken capabilities
        at startup.
     o  /bin/sh globbing and grep are old: no alternation in grep
        (use egrep), and ls with an unmatched glob can misreport.
     o  The libc predates strdup, memmove, and the POSIX sigset
        functions; termios lives in -lposix; setlocale in
        -lacomp (/usr/local/fd/lib).  Shims for all of these are in
        ~/se30 on the Mac.

FILES
     /.bashrc /.fvwmrc /.Xdefaults /.gtkrc /.x11start /.auxtoprc
     /usr/local/bin/{auxtop,auxtop-x,auxfont,dialc,dialc-x,rxvt}

